{"title": "Going home", "author": null, "url": "https://www.ukbonn.de/patient_innen/international/english/offers-and-services/going-home/", "hostname": "ukbonn.de", "description": null, "sitename": "UKB | UKB Startseite", "date": "2020-01-01", "id": null, "license": null, "body": null, "comments": "", "commentsbody": null, "raw_text": null, "text": "Going home\nWhen it's time to go home, you will of course, be given all the copies of the medical records made during your stay. If necessary, we can also help you to have your documents translated to your native language.\nWe can also arrange transport from your hotel or from University Hospital Bonn to the airport.\nWhen leaving the EU, you will not be required to pay duty on gifts, personal items or clothes. If you are carrying 10,000 euro or more in cash (or in other currencies or checks) on your person, you are required to report this to customs. Forms are available at the customs office at the airport.\nIf you are bringing valuable items with you to Germany (e.g. expensive equipment, watches or jewelleries), we advise you to present these items at the airport in your home country and complete the related documents. In this condition there will be no doubt regarding the origin of the items.\nFollowing the first examinations here in Bonn, you will receive another cost estimate for further medical treatment. This amount is due and payable during your stay. The final invoice will be issued after your treatment has been completed and your departure. If the invoice sum differs from the amount stated in the cost estimate, you will be refunded the difference or you will be requested to settle the amount still payable. All costs incurred can be settled in cash, bank transfer or by credit card.", "language": null, "image": "/site/templates/images/logos/UKB-Logo.png", "pagetype": "website", "links": ["#navigation", "https://www.ukbnewsroom.de/ukbpatientenkolloquium-2023/", "/patient_innen/international/", "/ueber-uns/pflege/"